A08:2025 Software or Data Integrity Failures !icon{: style="height:80px;width:80px" align="right"}
 Background. 
Software or Data Integrity Failures continues at 8, with a slight, clarifying name change from "Software and Data Integrity Failures". This category is focused on the failure to maintain trust boundaries and verify the integrity of software, code, and data artifacts at a lower level than Software Supply Chain Failures. This category focuses on making assumptions related to software updates and critical data, without verifying integrity. Notable Common Weakness Enumerations (CWEs) in

